General.Name: Tungsten Mining NL
General.Description: Tungsten Mining NL, a resources company, engages in the exploration, evaluation, and development of mineral projects in Australia. The company also explores for tungsten, molybdenum, gold, silver, bismuth, and fluorite deposits. It holds interest in the Mt Mulgine project located in the Murchison region of Western Australia. The company also owns interests in the Hatches Creek project consists of two exploration licenses covering 31.4 square kilometers situated in the Northern Territory of Australia; the Watershed project located in the North Queensland; the Big Hill project situated in the Eastern Pilbara; and the Kilba project located in the Ashburton region. Tungsten Mining NL was incorporated in 2011 and is based in West Perth, Australia.
